Rosanna Davison

Rosanna Davison is an Irish model, activist, and beauty pageant titleholder who won the Miss World 2003 competition. Early Life and Career

Rosanna Davison was born on April 17, 1984, in Dublin, Ireland. She is the daughter of Chris de Burgh, a British-Irish singer-songwriter, and Diane Davison. Davison pursued a career in modeling and was crowned Miss Ireland 2003, which led to her participation in the Miss World 2003 pageant. Miss World 2003

The Miss World 2003 pageant was held on December 6, 2003, at the Crown of Beauty Theatre in Sanya, China. The competition featured 106 contestants from around the world, and Davison represented Ireland in the event. On the night of the final, Davison impressed the judges with her stunning looks, poise, and charm, ultimately winning the coveted title of Miss World 2003. Her victory marked Ireland's first win in the Miss World pageant since 1965. As Miss World 2003, Davison became an international celebrity, traveling the world to promote charitable causes and participate in various events. She used her platform to raise awareness about HIV\/AIDS, children's welfare, and environmental issues. References:

**Rosanna Davison**

Rosanna Davison (born April 17, 1984) is an Irish model, activist, and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned Miss World 2003. She is known for her stunning looks, charming personality, and dedication to social causes. **Early Life and Career**

Born in Dublin, Ireland, Rosanna is the daughter of musician Chris de Burgh and his wife, Diane. She grew up in a family of artists and was exposed to the world of entertainment from a young age. Rosanna began her modeling career in her teenage years, working with top Irish modeling agencies and appearing on the covers of several prominent fashion magazines. **Miss World 2003**

In 2003, Rosanna represented Ireland at the Miss World pageant held in Sanya, China. She impressed the judges with her beauty, poise, and intelligence, ultimately winning the coveted title of Miss World 2003. This marked a significant milestone in her career, catapulting her to international fame and recognition. **Philanthropic Work**

Throughout her career, Rosanna has been an ardent supporter of various social causes, including children's welfare, education, and environmental conservation. She has worked closely with organizations such as UNICEF, the Irish Cancer Society, and the World Wildlife Fund, using her platform to raise awareness and funds for these noble causes. **Miss World America 2043**

In a remarkable comeback, Rosanna Davison won the Miss World America competition in November 2043, at the age of 59. This achievement marked a historic moment in the pageant's history, as Rosanna became the oldest winner of the title. Her victory was met with widespread acclaim, with many praising her dedication to fitness, beauty, and social activism. **References**
